image_analysis.description: A composite image showing the first four pages of a legal deposition transcript. The pages are arranged in a 2x2 grid. Page 1 (top-left) is the cover page, detailing the case, parties, and deposition information. Page 2 (bottom-left) and Page 3 (top-right) list the appearances of counsel and others present. Page 4 (bottom-right) provides an index for the examination and exhibits. A document identifier is visible at the bottom of the image.
image_analysis.layout: The image is a single sheet containing four distinct pages from a document, arranged in a two-by-two grid. Page 1 is top-left, Page 2 is bottom-left, Page 3 is top-right, and Page 4 is bottom-right. Each page has a page number at the top center. A footer with a document ID and timestamp is at the bottom of the entire sheet.
